I like monochrome icons in my status bar and the FDEMC icon was not cutting it. I made a replacement.

To install:

1. Download fdemc_icons.zip and upzip.

2. From Terminal, execute (each command should be on one line):

   MacOS X 10.6 (Snow Leopard)

   $ sudo cp /usr/local/ppc-3.2.0-190/bin/FDEStatusMenu.app/Contents/Resources/FDEEndpoint.png \
     /usr/local/ppc-3.2.0-190/bin/FDEStatusMenu.app/Contents/Resources/FDEEndpoint-orig.png

   $ sudo cp FDEEndpoint-custom.png \
     /usr/local/ppc-3.2.0-190/bin/FDEStatusMenu.app/Contents/Resources/FDEEndpoint.png

   MacOS X 10.7 (Lion)

   $ sudo cp /usr/local/ppc-3.3.4-224/bin/FDEStatusMenu.app/Contents/Resources/FDEEndpoint.png \
     /usr/local/ppc-3.3.4-224/bin/FDEStatusMenu.app/Contents/Resources/FDEEndpoint-original.png

   $ sudo cp FDEEndpoint-custom.png \
     /usr/local/ppc-3.3.4-224/bin/FDEStatusMenu.app/Contents/Resources/FDEEndpoint.png

3. Re-login
